  <reg:acttitle>Forest Act</reg:acttitle>
  <reg:title>Annual Rent Regulation</reg:title>
  <reg:amsincluded>[Last amended July 11, 2022 by B.C. Reg. 163/2022]</reg:amsincluded>
  <reg:regpitid>122_2003_pit</reg:regpitid>
  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d2e30">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Definitions</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>In this regulation:</bcl:text>
      <bcl:definition id="d0e42">
        <bcl:text>
          <in:term>Act</in:term> means the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96157_00" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Forest Act</in:doc></bcl:link>;</bcl:text>
      </bcl:definition>
      <bcl:definition id="d1e46">
        <bcl:text>
          <in:term>reduced volume condition</in:term> means a condition on a licence that, under section 14 (1) (g.2) of the Act, reduces a portion of the allowable annual cut available to the holder of the licence;</bcl:text>
      </bcl:definition>
      <bcl:definition id="d0e55">
        <bcl:text>
          <in:term>supplemental forest licence</in:term> has the same meaning as in section 14.2 (1) of the Act.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:definition>
      <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 190/2014, Sch. 2, s. 1; am. B.C. Reg. 163/2022, s. (a).]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d0e68">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Annual rent</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1.1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:subsection id="d1e71">
        <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>For the purposes of sections 111 and 112 of the Act, the holder of a licence, agreement or permit described in Column 1 of the following table must pay to the government annual rent at the rate set out in Column 2 immediately opposite that licence, agreement or permit:</bcl:text>
        <oasis:table style="2" id="d1e73">
          <oasis:tgroup cols="3" width="500">
            <oasis:colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" align="center" border="1"/>
            <oasis:colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" align="center" border="1"/>
            <oasis:colspec colname="c3" colnum="3" align="center" border="1"/>
            <oasis:thead>
              <oasis:trow>
                <oasis:entry colname="c1" align="center">
                  <oasis:line>Item</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
                <oasis:entry colname="c2" align="center">
                  <oasis:line> Column 1<in:br/><in:strong>Description of Licence,<in:br/> Agreement or Permit</in:strong></oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
                <oasis:entry colname="c3" align="center">
                  <oasis:line> Column 2<in:br/><in:strong>Rate of Annual Rent</in:strong></oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
              </oasis:trow>
            </oasis:thead>
            <oasis:tbody>
              <oasis:trow>
                <oasis:entry colname="c1" valign="center" align="center">
                  <oasis:line>1</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
                <oasis:entry colname="c2" valign="center">
                  <oasis:line>Community forest agreement</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
                <oasis:entry colname="c3" valign="center">
                  <oasis:line>$0.37/m<in:sup>3</in:sup> of allowable annual cut determined for the community forest agreement area</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
              </oasis:trow>
              <oasis:trow>
                <oasis:entry colname="c1" valign="center" align="center">
                  <oasis:line>2</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
                <oasis:entry colname="c2" valign="center">
                  <oasis:line>First nations woodland licence</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
                <oasis:entry colname="c3" valign="center">
                  <oasis:line>$0.12/m<in:sup>3</in:sup> of allowable annual cut determined for the first nations woodland licence area</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
              </oasis:trow>
              <oasis:trow>
                <oasis:entry colname="c1" valign="center" align="center">
                  <oasis:line>3</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
                <oasis:entry colname="c2" valign="center">
                  <oasis:line>Forest licence, other than a supplemental forest licence</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
                <oasis:entry colname="c3" valign="center">
                  <oasis:line>$0.37/m<in:sup>3</in:sup> of allowable annual cut specified in the forest licence</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
              </oasis:trow>
              <oasis:trow>
                <oasis:entry colname="c1" valign="center" align="center">
                  <oasis:line>4</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
                <oasis:entry colname="c2" valign="center">
                  <oasis:line>Cutting permit issued under a supplemental forest licence</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
                <oasis:entry colname="c3" valign="center">
                  <oasis:line>$0.37/m<in:sup>3</in:sup> of volume of timber authorized to be harvested under the cutting permit</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
              </oasis:trow>
              <oasis:trow>
                <oasis:entry colname="c1" valign="center" align="center">
                  <oasis:line>5</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
                <oasis:entry colname="c2" valign="center">
                  <oasis:line>Timber licence</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
                <oasis:entry colname="c3" valign="center">
                  <oasis:line>$1.85/ha</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
              </oasis:trow>
              <oasis:trow>
                <oasis:entry colname="c1" valign="center" align="center">
                  <oasis:line>6</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
                <oasis:entry colname="c2" valign="center">
                  <oasis:line>Tree farm licence</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
                <oasis:entry colname="c3" valign="center">
                  <oasis:line>$0.57/m<in:sup>3</in:sup> of allowable annual cut determined for the tree farm licence area</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
              </oasis:trow>
              <oasis:trow>
                <oasis:entry colname="c1" valign="center" align="center">
                  <oasis:line>7</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
                <oasis:entry colname="c2" valign="center">
                  <oasis:line>Woodlot licence</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
                <oasis:entry colname="c3" valign="center">
                  <oasis:line>$0.60/m<in:sup>3</in:sup> of allowable annual cut determined for the woodlot licence area</oasis:line>
                </oasis:entry>
              </oasis:trow>
            </oasis:tbody>
          </oasis:tgroup>
        </oasis:table>
      </bcl:subsection>
      <bcl:subsection id="d1e263">
        <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>Despite subsection (1), the holder of a licence with a reduced volume condition must pay an amount that corresponds to the portion of the allowable annual cut that is not reduced by the reduced volume condition.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:subsection>
      <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 190/2014, Sch. 2, s. 1; am. B.C. Reg. 163/2022, s. (b).]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e171">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Woodlot Product Development Council payment</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>With respect to a woodlot licence, $0.25/m<in:sup>3</in:sup> of the rate set out in Column 2 of the table in section 1.1 is allocated under section 112.1 of the Act to represent money payable to the Woodlot Product Development Council.</bcl:text>
      <bcl:hnote>[am. B.C. Reg. 190/2014, Sch. 2, s. 2.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
    <reg:provisionsnote>[Provisions relevant to the enactment of this regulation: <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96157_00" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Forest Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 157, ss. 11, 112 and 112.1.]</reg:provisionsnote>
  </reg:content>
</reg:regulation>